5 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING LAWS RELATED TO THE MEDICAL ASSISTANCE
6 PROGRAM; ESTABLISHING A MEDICAL ASSISTANCE PROGRAM FOR LICENSEES UNDER THE BOARD
7 OF CHIROPRACTORS AND THE BOARD OF VETERINARY MEDICINE; ESTABLISHING A FEE TO FUND
8 THE PROGRAM; AND AMENDING SECTIONS 37-1-131, 37-2-202, 37-2-316, AND 37-12-201, MCA.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Rehabilitation. (1) The board shall establish a medical assistance
13 program to assist licensees who are found to be physically or mentally impaired by habitual intemperance or
14 the excessive use of addictive drugs, alcohol, or any other drug or substance or by mental illness or chronic
15 physical illness. The program must provide for assistance to licensees in seeking treatment for mental illness or
16 substance abuse and monitor their efforts toward rehabilitation.
17 (2) The board shall ensure that a licensee who is required or volunteers to participate in the
18 medical assistance program as a condition of continued licensure or reinstatement of licensure must be allowed
19 to enroll in a qualified medical assistance program within this state and may not require a licensee to enroll in a
20 qualified treatment program outside the state unless the board finds that there is no qualified treatment program
21 in this state.
22 (3) For the purposes of funding this medical assistance program, the board shall adjust the
23 renewal fee to be commensurate with the cost of the program.
24
