12 Section 3. Section 37-2-202, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "37-2-202. Confidentiality of medical assistance program information -- health care
14 information. (1) The proceedings and records of a medical assistance program created in chapter 3, 4, 7, or 8,
15 12, or 18 relating to a licensee who has received or is receiving assistance from the medical assistance
16 program:
17 (a) are confidential and are considered to be proceedings and records of a professional standards
18 review committee under 37-2-201; and
19 (b) are not subject to discovery or introduction into evidence in any administrative or judicial
20 proceeding other than a disciplinary proceeding against the licensee before the applicable licensing board. If
21 the proceedings and records are introduced into evidence in a disciplinary proceeding, the introduced materials
22 are public unless otherwise protected by law.
23 (2) Any health care information, as defined in 50-16-803, that is maintained by a health care
24 provider in the provision of health care services to a licensee participating in a medical assistance program
25 provided for in chapter 3, 4, 7, or 8, 12, or 18 is subject to discovery from the licensee or the health care
26 provider and to introduction into evidence in an administrative or judicial proceeding as may otherwise be
27 allowed by law."
